Constructs a new item of Vector2D containing the elements in rhs.

The order of the elements in the new Vector2D is dependent on the iteration order of the seed collection.

Parameters:
rhsThe Vector2D to be copied from.
Warning:
Copy for Vector2D<TYPE> is different from Vector<Vector<TYPE> >. Both of them are shallow copy, but in different level.

template<class TYPE >
void gaia::base::Vector2D< TYPE >::insertAt ( size_t  index1,
size_t  index2,
const TYPE &  prototype_item,
size_t  numItems = 1 
)

Inserts the specified item into this vector at the specified location.

This item is inserted before any previous element at the specified location. All elements with an index equal or greater than location have their index increased by 1. If the location is equal to the size of this vector, the item is added at the end. The specified items are initialized from prototype items.

Parameters:
index1The Vector to be added to.
prototype_itemThe item to insert in this vector.
index2The index at which to insert the element.
numItemsNumber of items to be inserted.
See also:

size_t  index2,
const Vector< TYPE > &  vector 
)

Inserts the items in the specified vector at the specified location in this vector.

The items are inserted in the order in which they are returned from the vector iterator. The items with an index equal or higher than vector size have their index increased by the size of the added collection.

Parameters:
index1The Vector to be added to.
vectorGiven vector to be inserted into list vector.
index2The location to insert the items.
Returns:
True if this vector is modified, false otherwise.

template<class TYPE >
const Vector2D< TYPE > & gaia::base::Vector2D< TYPE >::operator= ( const Vector2D< TYPE > &  rhs)

Const-to-const assignment operation of vector.

Because copy-on-write mechanism, the original datum possesses by this vector is releaseed and this vector will acquire to possess datum on rhs vector.

Parameters:
rhsThe Vector2D to be copied from.
Warning:
Copy for Vector2D<TYPE> is different from Vector<Vector<TYPE> >. Both of them are shallow copy, but in different level.
